text: John Phillip Wingard (born August 26, 1927) is an American politician in the state of Minnesota. He served in the Minnesota House of Representatives from 1963–1964, 1965–1966, and 1967–1972. WIngard attended the University of Minnesota and was a potato farmer. ==References== Category:1927 births Category:Living people Category:Members of the Minnesota House of Representatives
